<font color="#FF0000">TOKATA</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 11 22:43:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Humming Eagle,<br><br>
The warrior with the &quot;most spiritual, emotional and         physical wounds is weakened&quot;, but, on the other hand, I can see as strengthened as well. For a warrior to know his weaknesses and can deal with them is to be stronger than those who know nothing of themselves at all.<br><br>
We know ourselves through the trial of war.<br><br>
The other way of the seer, the sacred man, the healer, other forms of strength born of wounds, I see is a continuation of the honor and worth of the warrior by his people. All warriors have honor and worth, no matter how they are diminished, until they know in their hearts it is time to go on the other journey.<br><br>
The other journey beckoned to me once. I said &quot;I am not ready. I now know myself through the trial of war, and I am strong.&quot; <br><br>
I can be both warrior and healer if I am strong, but I must heal myself first. I feel this is a good way and the correct way to journey. It has a future...tokata! <br><br>
Hecito Yelo, my Brother of Choice.
<p><code>--   (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


